Movement keys :
---------------
Directional keys or keypad : move around (keep <Shift> pressed to speed up)
<PageUp> / <+> : move up a z-level
<PageDown> / <-> : move down a z-level
<Insert> : peek at the upper level (while pressed)
<Delete> : peek at the lower level (while pressed)

Actions :
---------
<Return> / <Enter> : begin selection / apply action
<Escape> : cancel selection
<Ctrl-Z> : undo
<Ctrl-Y> : redo
<Ctrl-X> : cut
<Ctrl-C> : copy
<Ctrl-V> : paste

Selection modes :
-----------------
<Shift-R> : full rectangle mode
<Shift-C> : empty rectangle mode
<Shift-E> : full ellipse mode
<Shift-O> : one tile mode
<Shift-P> : protect mode (dig without clearing stairs, etc)

Modes :
-------
(dig > items > stockpiles > adjust > dig)
<Shift-M> : next mode
<Shift-N> : previous mode

Files :
-------
<Ctrl-N> : new file
<Ctrl-S> : save file
<Ctrl-L> : load file
<Ctrl-Shift-L> : insert file at cursor
<Ctrl-Q> : quit

Miscellaneous :
---------------
<Shift-H> : show / hide crosshairs
<Shift-G> : show / hide ghost levels
<Shift-X> : define the blueprint start point
<Shift-W> : show / hide the start point

Other :
-------
The coordinates are displayed at the bottom right :
Position : P: (X,Y,Z)
Selection : S: (X,Y,Z) -- C: tiles
